<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1563">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/399.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Panama</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 20.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Panama</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your excellency’s note of May 13, in which you inform me
                            [etc.]</p>
                        <p>Immediately upon receipt of that communication I telegraphed the
                            substance of it to my Government, which will doubtless fully appreciate
                            this additional proof of the solicitude of your excellency’s Government
                            for the orderly and constitutional development of the Government of the
                            Republic.</p>
                        <p>I beg your excellency to express to the President my sincere thanks for
                            having favorably considered the desires of my Government, for which I am
                            also grateful to your excellency.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ricardo Arias.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>